# .ci-ignore-warnings
# Patterns listed here are approved exceptions to the CI warning gate.
# One pattern per line. Lines starting with # are comments. Blank lines ignored.
# Patterns are matched as substrings against warning annotation text.
#
# POLICY: Every entry MUST have a comment explaining why it is accepted
# and (where applicable) a linked issue for eventual resolution.
#
# ── Currently accepted warnings ──────────────────────────────────────────────

# DeprecationWarning from third-party libraries in pytest output.
# These are in upstream packages we don't control; tracked in deps upgrade cycle.
DeprecationWarning

# pytest-asyncio mode warning — requires config change in pyproject.toml.
# Accepted until pytest-asyncio config is standardized.
PytestUnraisableExceptionWarning

# npm peer dependency warnings from --legacy-peer-deps installs.
# Our frontend dependency tree has peer conflicts that are safe but noisy.
# Tracked: resolve peer deps in next frontend dependency audit pass.
npm warn ERESOLVE

# ResourceWarning from SQLite connections in test teardown.
# Harmless — SQLite file descriptors, not a leak in production code.
ResourceWarning
